 |accessdate=2009-05-30 
 }}</ref><ref name="nrhpinv">{{citation|title={{PDFlink|[http://pdfhost.focus.nps.gov/docs/NHLS/Text/70000423.pdf National Register of Historic Places Inventory-Nomination: Central Synagogue]|220 KB}}|author=Carolyn Pitts|date=February 2, 1975|publisher=National Park Service}} and {{PDFlink|[http://pdfhost.focus.nps.gov/docs/NHLS/Photos/70000423.pdf ''Accompanying 5 photos, exterior and interior, from 1973 and undated'']|1.53 MB}}</ref>  It has been restored recently in the original style after a fire in August 1998.<ref name="1000nycbldg">'''Harris, Bill; ''One Thousand New York Buildings''''', 1st Edition; Black Dog and Leventhal. 2002. ISBN 1-57912-443-7; p.272.</ref>，每周定时向公众开放游览。

这座犹太会堂拥有著名的布鲁克林Salem Fields Cemetery。 

